{"url": "https://www.reddit.com/r/learnprogramming/comments/9b0xkm/need_help_with_merging_in_subversion/", "text": "Hey all. I checked out a copy of trunk to create Branch A. I did work on Branch A, am satisfied with my work, and need to create a Branch B before I continue. I want to use 'svn merge' to make my Branch B exactly as my Branch A is. \n\nHow can I do this? I tried searching for the answer myself  but only ended up getting more confused. Thanks for your help in advance.", "score": 1, "comments": [{"body": "Don't use `svn merge`, just make a copy of your branch and be done with it:\n\n    svn cp ^/branches/branch_a ^/branches/branch_b", "id": "e4zjgno", "replies": [{"body": "Ah, didn\u2019t even know that was an option. Thank you!", "id": "e4zjj5j", "replies": []}]}], "title": "Need help with merging in Subversion"}